text.paragraph:
Misuse or abuse of EXALGO by crushing, chewing, snorting, or injecting the dissolved product will result in the uncontrolled delivery of the opioid and pose a significant risk that could result in overdose and death [see
                            Overdosage (10)
                           ].

EXALGO may cause severe hypotension including orthostatic hypotension and syncope in ambulatory patients. There is an increased risk in patients whose ability to maintain blood pressure has already been compromised by a reduced blood volume or concurrent administration of certain CNS depressant drugs (e.g. phenothiazines or general anesthetics) [see 
                           Drug Interactions (7.1)
                           ]. Monitor these patients for signs of hypotension after initiating or titrating the dose of EXALGO.
